I, 6, 131</bibl> etc. <cit><quote>all in h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 870" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 870</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in all h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 14</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 1, 57</bibl>. <cit><quote>in all swift h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 119</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in such h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 2</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.104" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 104</bibl>. <cit><quote>in the h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 1, 26</bibl></cit>. <emph>in h. whereof</emph> (== to do so speedily) <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.150" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 150</bibl>. <emph>to be in h.</emph> == to have no time to lose: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 3, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.161" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 161</bibl> etc. <cit><quote>I am in great h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 4, 174</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.5.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 5, 54</bibl>. cf. <cit><quote>here comes one in h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.2.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 2, 96</bibl></cit> (one who has no time to lose). <cit><quote>nature, rather curious than in h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 2, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with h.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.378" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 378</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.43" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.167" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.3.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 3, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.309" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 309</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.238" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 238</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.236" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 236</bibl>. <cit><quote>to have h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 47</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to make h.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.190" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 4, 190</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.258" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 258</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 1, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.327" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 327</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.454" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 454</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">2, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 13</bibl> etc. <cit><quote>make good h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.5.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 5, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>make your best h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 3, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>make your soonest h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.4.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 4, 27</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>make all the speedy h. you may,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 60</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>put it to the h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 196</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>let him take his h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 213</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Post-haste</emph>).
